# Dhee_AI Engineering Constitution (binding)

This repository IS the engineering constitution of Dhee_AI. The specification is the
single source of truth. Read [ENGINEERING_CONSTITUTION.md](../../ENGINEERING_CONSTITUTION.md)
and [CLAUDE.md](../../CLAUDE.md) before making any change.

## Document precedence (highest wins)
1. Engineering Constitution -> 2. Architecture -> 3. ADR Decisions -> 4. Product Requirements
-> 5. Roadmap -> 6. Milestones -> 7. Implementation.
Earlier documents win unless an ADR in `DECISIONS.md` explicitly supersedes them.

## Non-negotiable rules
- Never violate the Engineering Constitution or the architecture.
- Implementation follows specification; specification never follows implementation.
- No new behavior without first updating the relevant specification (Living Specification Rule).
- No placeholder implementations where a practical one is possible.
- Strict TypeScript, fully typed public APIs. No `any` in shipped code.
- Every feature ships with tests (unit + integration + e2e where relevant) and documentation.
- Respect module boundaries; never introduce cyclic dependencies.
- Prefer composition over inheritance and interfaces over concrete implementations.
- Never move files without updating every reference. Keep commits atomic.
- Never duplicate business logic.

## Before coding (autonomous workflow, never skipped)
read specs -> plan -> verify dependencies -> check architecture boundaries -> validate
against principles -> implement -> tests -> docs -> self-review -> verify Constitution compliance.

## Definition of Done
Spec updated, ADR added when required, docs complete, tests passing, API documented,
security reviewed, performance evaluated, accessibility reviewed, backward compatibility
verified, CI passing. Anything less is incomplete.
